Dancers of Frieda’s Dance Studio attained several trophies and medals at the Bosveld Kunsfees recently held in the city.
They competed against tens of other dancers from across the province. Cara Coetzee and Emma Ströh were announced best tap dancing duet and scored 100%.
Palesa Masimene and her sister, Bokang also performed well and achieved 86% in the category for modern dancing duet. Palesa won individual trophies for solo tap dancing (98%) as well as modern improvisation (94%) and was awarded for her outstanding personality in the junior category.
Story and photos: RC Myburgh
